The Vlakfontein man accused of killing his girlfriend and burying her under his bed remains behind bars. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The Vlakfontein man accused of killing his girlfriend and burying her under his bed remains behind bars. Thokozani Sibeko appeared briefly in the Protea magistrate’s court in Soweto on Tuesday. READ: Woman's body found under boyfriend's bed in Vlakfontein His bail application is set for 20 August. Police are still trying to locate the deceased's family while the community wants justice. READ: Vlakfontein murder accused to appear in court Residents said Sibeko shouldn't receive bail because he is a danger to society. Vlakfontein is the same area where seven family members were found murderedand buried in a house last year.